Generic single-database configuration for app-aws-s3-files.

This Alembic setup manages database migrations for the app-aws-s3-files FastAPI application.

Key Features:

- App-specific version table: alembic_version_aws_s3_files
- Namespace prefix: aws*s3_files* for all tables
- Upgrade-only migrations (no automatic downgrades)
- Integration with app settings via POSTGRES\_\* environment variables

Usage:
make -f Makefile.Alembic db-status # Check migration status
make -f Makefile.Alembic db-upgrade # Apply pending migrations
make -f Makefile.Alembic db-create MSG='description' # Create new migration

See Makefile.Alembic for full command reference.

Important Rules:

1. All table names must use 'aws*s3_files*' prefix (e.g., aws_s3_files_metadata, aws_s3_files_uploads)
2. All indexes must use 'ix*aws_s3_files*' prefix
3. All foreign keys must use 'fk*aws_s3_files*' prefix
4. Migrations are upgrade-only (downgrade functions contain only 'pass')
5. Use POSTGRES\_\* system environment variables (no .env files)

Note: This app primarily manages S3 files and may not need database tables.
Only create migrations if persistent metadata storage is required.
